e Knights<br><br>Today I speak to you as an officer. As of January 5th, 2002 Earth Date, the Knights of Freedom have moved into a new era. As the new year was ushered in, the leadership of this guild understood and saw that there was a need for change. In the following days to come, you loyal members will be seeing new mandates, sections on the board, and general changes to the every day operations of the Knights.<br><br>Over the past few months of 2001, the KoF has seen a large section of its' most seasoned knights either move on to better things or have retired due to other circumstances. As the smoke cleared, the KoF was left with a small but dedicated core of players. That core is you, my fellow knights, and it is to you that I direct this message at.<br><br>In the past, the KoF has always been a good group of indiviuals banded together with a common goal of fun, family, and loyalty. Yet today, the leadership of the guild wishes to ask the members of the KoF to help us build on this family, and drive the KoF forward towards a greater community.<br><br>We call upon all the loyal members to keep an open mind to the new changes that will pop up over the days to come. You will be asked to donate your time, effort, and if need be, material gains to an end that will allow the guild to grow as a whole. Most importantly, you will be asked to be a contributing member of our community. For if the guild grows, you will grow as a character and as a player. Loyalty, patience, and integrity will all be noted.<br><br>For better or ill, these changes will happen, and it is my wish that you will find most if not all these changes to your liking. However understand this, every change and action is done for the entire betterment of the guild and a greater sense of community between our allies and ourselves.<br><br>Thank you for your time.<br><br>Senaan Truesilver<br>A champion and an officer of the Knights<br>Loving husband of Joslin Truesilver<br> <p></p><i></i>